JOHANNESBURG - Motorists will cough up more for fuel from 4 April. The price of petrol will increase by between 69 and 72 cents per litre.  The diesel price will go up by 65 cents.  READ:Â Big spike in petrol price The increases include the fuel levy announced during the budget speech in February. The steady rand and an increase in oil prices have also contributed to the higher fuel price. The petrol price increase comes on the back of the 1 April VAT increase. eNCA